    <descript>
      <abstract>End-of-winter snow depth and average snow density from area A, B, C and D, which include 1000's of point depth measurement located between ~20 and ~50 cm apart. Dataset DOI: http://dx.doi.org/10.5440/1236472</abstract>
      <purpose>Data were collected to quantify the spatiotemporal variation in end-of-winter snow accumulation across varying ice-wedge polygon types.</purpose>
    </descript>
