    <lineage>
      <method>
        <methtype>field</methtype>
        <methdesc>The depth measurements were made using a GPS snow depth probe (http://www.snowhydro.com/products/column2.html). The corner coordinates of the entire domain were determined using a differential GPS (DGPS) by Ulrich. In the field, the exact location of the start- and end of respective transect was determined using a measurement tape that was laid out between the south (and north) grid corners. The coordinates derived from individual GPS snow probe measurements were then post-processed by applying the average offset of the x- and y locations at respective transect's start- and end point (in order to produce refined coordinates of individual points).</methdesc>
      </method>
